                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " A deuterium beam energy of 2 MeV and a beam",
                " current of 20 uA to bombard a tritium target,",
                " generating monoenergetic neutrons."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "ThO2 powder with a purity of 99.9% was pressed into",
                " three disks with a diameter of 20 mm and density of",
                " 0.1998 g/cm2. The weight of thorium were 0.627, 0.630,",
                " 0.635 g, respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " An ORTEC high-purity germanium detector with",
                " about 50% relative efficiency was used to measure the",
                " gamma radioactivity of the activated samples. The",
                " energy resolution of this detector for 1332 keV gamma",
                " rays is 1.8 keV. For energy calibration and",
                " efficiency calibration, standard sources such as 60Co,",
                " 152Eu, 133Ba, 166mHo, 137Cs, and 241Am were used."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "LONGC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A BF3 long neutron counter, to monitor",
                " changes in neutron flux online during irradiation."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The three samples were irradiated for 4.219 h."
              ]
            }
